[Notes]
- doesn't rely on consecutive blocks - fragmentation no longer a problem
- disk.c/disk.h only provide primitives to read and write entire blocks (4096 bytes)
- directory holds entry with file name, length, and head of file
- superblock - information where to find directory and FAT